Reasoning: 

1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper examines the role of social structures in web user behavior, specifically in the context of online censorship in China. It analyzes audience traffic among the 1000 most visited websites and identifies clusters based on language and geography, which is a key aspect of social networks. 

2. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper explores the societal impact of Internet censorship in China and challenges the dominant discourse on the subject. It also discusses the role of cultural factors in shaping web user behavior, which is a key aspect of the intersection between computers and society. 

3. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper touches upon language as a factor in web user behavior, as it identifies language-based clusters among the most visited websites. It also discusses the role of cultural proximity in shaping online behaviors, which is relevant to the study of natural language processing and computational linguistics. 

4. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper does not focus on software engineering per se, but it does touch upon the technical aspects of Internet censorship and access blockage. It also discusses the implications of these technical measures on web user behavior, which is relevant to the design and development of software systems.
